WEBVTT

00:56.090 --> 00:58.968
FILING FOR LOVE

01:53.772 --> 01:54.940
What kind of dream was that?

02:05.534 --> 02:06.535
Did you get some rest?

02:06.952 --> 02:09.663
Don't forget to come in
at the usual time today. Good luck.

02:09.955 --> 02:11.665
Oh, right. Work.

02:13.876 --> 02:15.836
No wonder I had that terrible dream.

02:30.976 --> 02:33.312
Here's your iced Americano.

02:35.189 --> 02:36.231
Mr. Noh.

02:36.607 --> 02:38.942
- Are you okay now?
- What do you mean?

02:39.026 --> 02:41.236
When there was a ruckus outside
two days ago

02:41.612 --> 02:43.530
you passed out in shock.

02:43.906 --> 02:47.493
The photos are everywhere.
They call you the Haemu Fainter.

02:48.535 --> 02:50.496
I heard the affair was real.

02:50.829 --> 02:52.706
So her husband is
Mr. Son from Food Brand Planning?

02:53.415 --> 02:55.376
What happens to them now?

02:55.584 --> 02:58.003
You handle the employees' affairs...

02:58.087 --> 02:59.380
- Da-yeong.
- Yes?

03:00.005 --> 03:01.715
I think your orders
are pretty backed up.

03:02.383 --> 03:03.801
I'm so sorry.

03:08.764 --> 03:10.140
Hey, Mr. Noh.

03:10.933 --> 03:12.017
The Haemu Fainter.

03:13.769 --> 03:15.854
You look fine. Are you all right now?

03:15.938 --> 03:17.147
- I'm fine.
- Good.

03:17.231 --> 03:19.858
I heard you're in charge of affairs.
How did that happen?

03:19.942 --> 03:21.694
- I thought you were some big shot.
- Hey.

03:22.945 --> 03:24.530
I handle PM cases, not affairs.

03:24.738 --> 03:26.490
And the term is
"personal misconduct."

03:27.324 --> 03:28.492
You're just clueless.

03:36.417 --> 03:37.668
Mr. Noh.

03:42.589 --> 03:43.590
Yes, Ms. Park.

03:43.882 --> 03:46.301
I heard what happened.
Are you all right?

03:47.302 --> 03:48.345
I'm fine.

03:48.887 --> 03:50.013
That's good to hear.

03:57.730 --> 03:59.356
Hey, there, Mr. Noh.

03:59.857 --> 04:01.066
Are you just clocking in?

04:01.442 --> 04:03.485
I'm so pleased to see you,
I could faint.

04:06.864 --> 04:07.865
Ms. Joo.

04:08.741 --> 04:10.534
You can't tease me about that.

04:11.410 --> 04:13.203
Why not? Don't I have the right?

04:13.537 --> 04:16.165
The only reason you're fine
without a single scratch

04:16.373 --> 04:19.334
is that I caught you like this
with my two arms as you fell.

04:19.752 --> 04:21.837
You know I saved you, right?

04:23.464 --> 04:25.215
I sprained my wrist a bit,
so I got some acupuncture.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.218
Sure, I can't thank you enough.

04:28.510 --> 04:29.636
It's nothing, really.

04:32.014 --> 04:34.808
I'll type up a report on what action
to take against Mr. Son.

04:35.559 --> 04:37.186
I took care of that already.

04:37.811 --> 04:38.854
What?

04:39.855 --> 04:41.190
I closed that case.

04:44.860 --> 04:47.029
Mouthwatering and mellow,
here's Masigo.

04:47.446 --> 04:50.282
With Haemu's own
innovative food technology

04:50.365 --> 04:53.660
Masigo succeeded to realize
the farm-to-table notion

04:53.744 --> 04:55.287
and we're confident it will become

04:55.370 --> 04:58.207
a brand that represents Haemu
and leads global food trends.

04:58.499 --> 05:00.667
That concludes the presentation.
Thanks for listening.

05:05.172 --> 05:06.215
Thank you.

05:12.679 --> 05:13.722
Thank you.

05:14.014 --> 05:15.349
I'll do my best.

05:20.562 --> 05:22.773
Even so, that's not right, Ms. Joo.

05:23.774 --> 05:26.819
How could Ms. Jeong be demoted
to a plant while Mr. Son remains?

05:27.027 --> 05:28.695
And he gets to keep his project?

05:29.780 --> 05:32.574
If we must decide who did worse,
Ms. Jeong is single

05:32.658 --> 05:34.326
while Mr. Son's married,
so he did more harm.

05:34.409 --> 05:36.245
Who did Mr. Son cause harm to?

05:37.496 --> 05:39.331
Mr. Son always did well at work

05:39.414 --> 05:41.625
and he's in charge of a new brand
the Food Team has invested in.

05:42.000 --> 05:43.210
What about Ms. Jeong?

05:43.293 --> 05:45.045
All she did was play a part
in Mr. Son's project.

05:45.128 --> 05:46.588
Her performance and reputation
are below his.

05:47.464 --> 05:48.757
From the company's point of view

05:48.841 --> 05:51.176
Ms. Jeong has done more harm
than Mr. Son.

05:51.760 --> 05:52.803
Am I wrong?

05:54.388 --> 05:55.597
Still, morally speaking...

06:00.394 --> 06:01.436
Morals?

06:01.979 --> 06:03.856
Do you think
you're a police officer or a judge?

06:04.147 --> 06:06.942
Do companies reward the good
and punish the bad?

06:07.234 --> 06:09.361
A company only has to care

06:09.444 --> 06:11.905
about the profit or loss
caused by an employee.

06:11.989 --> 06:14.825
Because here,
that is our ethics and morals.

06:24.251 --> 06:25.335
What is it?

06:25.419 --> 06:27.421
Did you hope
for an exhilarating resolution?

06:27.921 --> 06:30.591
For a cheating couple
to be humiliated out of their jobs?

06:33.176 --> 06:34.720
You're more naive than you look.

06:36.430 --> 06:37.723
Why did you put me in charge?

06:41.018 --> 06:42.060
This duty

06:43.395 --> 06:45.272
doesn't suit me because I'm naive.

06:51.445 --> 06:52.571
No, you're perfect for the job.

06:52.654 --> 06:55.032
- Ms. Joo, what on earth...
- Don't get too upset.

06:55.115 --> 06:57.159
Mr. Son got a bigger percentage
of his pay docked.

06:57.534 --> 07:00.412
Not to mention that this incident
ruined his reputation for good.

07:00.495 --> 07:02.998
It will be taken into consideration
at his next performance review.

07:03.498 --> 07:06.001
Plus, there are legal repercussions
if he's sued for divorce.

07:08.211 --> 07:10.589
There, let's forget
about a closed case.

07:10.672 --> 07:12.257
Do your next assignment right.

07:12.466 --> 07:13.467
Sorry?

07:17.012 --> 07:18.013
"Work.com."

07:18.513 --> 07:20.265
You should check it out.
The comments are insane.

07:50.128 --> 07:54.800
EPISODE 2:
I AM THE BEST

07:55.384 --> 07:57.511
Seriously, do something about Zone F.

07:57.594 --> 07:59.262
It's basically a love motel in Haemu.

07:59.596 --> 08:01.473
- It's like watching porn.
- "Zone F"?

08:01.556 --> 08:02.641
So everyone knows it.

08:02.975 --> 08:04.559
The head office's
basement parking lot.

08:05.143 --> 08:07.854
- It probably has no cameras.
- What is this about?

08:07.938 --> 08:09.231
I never park there.

08:09.314 --> 08:10.691
Is this news to you?

08:11.942 --> 08:14.403
It's Zone F in level four
of the basement parking lot.

08:15.070 --> 08:17.072
It's the spot
for couples in the company

08:17.155 --> 08:19.032
whether they're dating
morally or immorally.

08:19.574 --> 08:22.452
It's dark with no cameras
pointing that way

08:22.703 --> 08:24.246
and not many park that far down.

08:24.663 --> 08:25.747
It's perfect.

08:25.998 --> 08:28.083
You seem to know a lot, Mr. Cha.

08:28.166 --> 08:30.711
That's what I heard
through the grapevine.

08:31.586 --> 08:33.046
Let's check the facts first.

08:33.505 --> 08:35.424
We can't investigate
based on a rumor.

08:35.507 --> 08:36.633
- Yes, sir.
- Okay?

08:36.717 --> 08:38.343
Check facts? With whom?

08:39.136 --> 08:40.762
Our team has set up

08:40.846 --> 08:43.306
- a humint network.
- What? "Humint"?

08:43.390 --> 08:44.433
INFO GATHERED FROM INFORMANTS

08:44.516 --> 08:47.227
- Yes.
- Gosh, don't even talk about it.

08:47.310 --> 08:48.520
There's no end to it.

08:48.603 --> 08:51.481
It's embarrassing for both parties
if we catch them in the act.

08:52.024 --> 08:53.525
We just turn a blind eye.

08:53.608 --> 08:56.695
I heard Zone F is the place to go.

08:56.778 --> 08:59.906
BASEMENT PARKING CLOSED
FOR REPAIR WORK

08:59.990 --> 09:01.033
It's that spot over there.

09:01.908 --> 09:04.036
Is it more thrilling
if they do it there?

09:04.578 --> 09:07.039
I don't know why people
with decent jobs would do that.

09:09.082 --> 09:10.375
I wonder myself.

09:10.459 --> 09:12.627
If you see anything suspicious

09:12.711 --> 09:14.004
please report it to us.

09:14.087 --> 09:16.923
- Sure thing. Take care, then.
- Thank you.

09:19.760 --> 09:23.346
Our humint network confirmed
the rumor is true.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.685
Humint, my foot.

09:30.687 --> 09:32.564
- Let's go eat.
- Okay.

09:32.647 --> 09:35.275
The cafeteria's serving pork cutlet,
doenjang soup

09:35.358 --> 09:36.443
- braised potatoes...
- Not there.

09:36.526 --> 09:38.653
I'll check my list
of nearby restaurants.

09:39.029 --> 09:40.280
Don't bother.

09:45.202 --> 09:47.746
THIS EVENING

09:52.459 --> 09:54.127
What are you doing today?
It's your birthday.

09:54.795 --> 09:55.921
Did your boyfriend schedule a date?

09:56.755 --> 09:57.756
Well...

09:57.839 --> 09:59.966
Why are you so mysterious?

10:00.217 --> 10:03.053
I'm curious what kind of guy
girls like you date.

10:41.216 --> 10:43.552
Why does the cafeteria food
get worse by the day?

10:43.718 --> 10:46.138
- Right? Let's eat out tomorrow.
- Okay.

10:46.429 --> 10:47.889
- Ms. Yeon.
- What?

10:47.973 --> 10:50.392
Isn't that Mr. Kwon, your husband?

10:51.059 --> 10:52.269
Yes, that's right.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.062
Why don't you even say hi?

10:54.855 --> 10:55.981
Did you two fight?

10:57.357 --> 10:59.109
We didn't fight. We get along fine.

10:59.442 --> 11:01.528
Ji-yeon, wait until you get married.

11:01.611 --> 11:02.654
After just a few years

11:02.904 --> 11:04.531
you flinch
when your hands accidentally touch.

11:05.031 --> 11:06.074
That's an exaggeration.

11:09.744 --> 11:11.037
You two are hilarious.

11:11.371 --> 11:13.582
Before you got married,
you didn't say hi

11:13.665 --> 11:15.000
because you were dating in secret.

11:15.083 --> 11:16.751
But now,
everyone knows you're married.

11:17.294 --> 11:18.587
Are you shy now that you're married?

11:18.670 --> 11:20.213
We're keeping work
and personal lives separate.

11:20.964 --> 11:24.259
You speak as if
your private life is pretty eventful.

11:27.095 --> 11:28.096
Hey.

11:29.055 --> 11:30.098
Do you guys even do it?

11:30.599 --> 11:31.600
Stop it.

11:32.517 --> 11:33.977
You don't do that with family.

11:35.896 --> 11:37.314
You used to be so fired up.

11:38.106 --> 11:39.816
Why does it die
once people get married?

11:40.275 --> 11:42.319
You burn to death
if you stay fired up.

11:51.119 --> 11:52.787
NEW MESSAGE FROM YEON
FROM GENERAL AFFAIRS

11:54.122 --> 11:56.249
I'm meeting old friends from school
and will be home late.

11:57.709 --> 11:58.793
Okay.

12:13.808 --> 12:15.644
Oh, dear. I'm so sorry, Mr. Kwon.

12:16.311 --> 12:19.022
- It's okay.
- I'm so stupid.

12:19.105 --> 12:20.857
I'm really sorry.

12:20.941 --> 12:22.692
Don't be. It happens.

12:24.027 --> 12:25.028
Ms. Seon?

12:25.570 --> 12:26.738
I'm coming, sir.

12:27.280 --> 12:28.448
- Sorry.
- Go ahead.

12:51.304 --> 12:53.098
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

12:58.061 --> 12:59.604
I'm loving this.

13:00.105 --> 13:01.231
- Right?
- Jun-seo!

13:01.898 --> 13:04.192
- Over here.
- He looks even better now.

13:04.276 --> 13:06.319
- Long time no see.
- You haven't changed at all.

13:06.528 --> 13:09.239
Sorry, I forgot to tell you
he was coming.

13:10.782 --> 13:11.825
Don't worry.

13:12.075 --> 13:13.785
It's been ages since we broke up.

13:22.168 --> 13:23.628
It has been a while, So-young.

13:23.962 --> 13:25.005
Yes.

13:25.213 --> 13:27.048
You look just the same.

13:27.716 --> 13:28.758
You haven't changed.

13:30.051 --> 13:32.345
I'm not the same. I got old, right?

13:32.429 --> 13:33.513
No.

13:33.847 --> 13:35.598
You're pretty. Just like before.

13:36.725 --> 13:39.144
- What's going on here?
- You're prettier now.

13:39.936 --> 13:42.147
- You're just the same.
- I lost my appetite.

13:42.981 --> 13:44.566
- Sorry.
- Pour me a drink?

13:45.066 --> 13:46.109
Here.

13:47.777 --> 13:48.903
Let's begin.

13:54.993 --> 13:56.453
You can vote now.

13:56.536 --> 13:58.038
FINAL RESULT
OF THE THIRD SURVIVOR

13:59.039 --> 14:00.248
Why did his ranking drop?

14:00.332 --> 14:03.251
Vote for the person
who stole your heart.

14:05.170 --> 14:07.005
The mission benefit is too great.

14:07.088 --> 14:10.633
BOYS II PLANET's first round
of the final global vote is now open.

14:11.509 --> 14:13.178
BOYS II PLANET's final global...

14:13.261 --> 14:14.971
Can I vote for the same person twice?

14:15.055 --> 14:16.765
Log onto the BOYS II PLANET site

14:17.724 --> 14:18.892
and click "vote"

14:19.434 --> 14:21.561
- then select one participant.
- Who's that?

14:26.691 --> 14:28.985
Hi. Let's have a drink.
It's been a while.

14:41.498 --> 14:43.833
What are you up to?
Do you want to get back with me?

14:45.335 --> 14:46.419
Do you want to?

14:47.504 --> 14:48.630
Forget it, then.

14:49.798 --> 14:52.717
Gosh.
You're really one-sidedly one-sided.

14:53.343 --> 14:55.678
You asked me out
then suddenly ghosted me.

14:56.304 --> 14:58.181
Now you barge in after two years

14:58.556 --> 15:00.183
- and want a drink?
- So what?

15:00.767 --> 15:02.310
Were you sad that I dumped you?

15:03.144 --> 15:04.354
Did you cry over me?

15:05.230 --> 15:06.523
You didn't.

15:06.606 --> 15:09.067
"If you want to leave, go ahead.
I won't hold you back."

15:09.651 --> 15:11.945
I bet you didn't even shed a tear.

15:12.779 --> 15:14.280
Here. have a drink and call it even.

15:26.042 --> 15:27.043
It's good, isn't it?

15:29.337 --> 15:30.505
It's not bad.

15:32.298 --> 15:33.967
Let me stay for a while.

15:35.468 --> 15:37.262
- What?
- Let me stay here.

15:38.054 --> 15:39.347
The whiskey's the rent.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.099
This costs over three million won.

15:41.182 --> 15:43.351
Hey, what kind of nonsense is this?

15:43.852 --> 15:45.895
Get out. This isn't a boarding house.

15:45.979 --> 15:47.814
I really don't have a place to go.

15:48.064 --> 15:51.526
I had to leave my old place
and I couldn't find a new place yet.

15:51.818 --> 15:53.278
You know that my family...

15:54.279 --> 15:55.947
They're no help to me at all.

15:57.657 --> 15:59.200
I get that you're in a tough spot...

15:59.451 --> 16:02.078
You can't barge
into a guy's bachelor pad.

16:04.956 --> 16:06.749
- I'll get you a hotel room.
- For how long?

16:07.167 --> 16:08.710
Who knows how long I'll need?

16:09.252 --> 16:10.378
Do you have ten million won?

16:15.884 --> 16:17.635
I guess you can't help me.

16:18.303 --> 16:19.929
I get it. I'll leave.

16:20.805 --> 16:24.434
I'll stay at a sauna
or end up on some street corner.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.228
And if a creepy guy hits on me?

16:27.312 --> 16:29.230
I'll go with him. I can't be picky.

16:30.565 --> 16:31.608
Goodbye.

16:42.577 --> 16:43.661
It's only for the time being.

16:44.329 --> 16:45.747
Leave as soon as you can.

16:49.667 --> 16:52.128
I'll take the small room.
You can take the big room.

16:56.674 --> 16:59.177
Wait, isn't that a given?

17:02.388 --> 17:04.015
How brazen.

17:11.022 --> 17:13.107
Take a look at the shower head.
It's leaking again.

17:14.526 --> 17:15.652
Okay, I will.

17:17.820 --> 17:19.322
You say that and do nothing.

17:20.698 --> 17:21.741
Goodness.

17:22.534 --> 17:25.828
Did you read about Zone F online?

17:27.580 --> 17:29.040
Yes, I did.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.585
Some people have too much energy.

17:33.169 --> 17:35.922
They do something at work
that we don't even do in bed.

17:53.773 --> 17:54.816
Shall we do it?

17:59.904 --> 18:01.406
I'm tired.

18:06.119 --> 18:07.704
I wasn't interested, either.

18:09.122 --> 18:10.164
Turn off the light.

18:10.498 --> 18:11.749
You do it.

18:28.725 --> 18:31.060
You've lost weight.
Your face got smaller.

18:32.228 --> 18:34.230
Are you stressed out
because of Joo In-a?

18:36.232 --> 18:37.900
Drink the whiskey you brought.

18:37.984 --> 18:39.152
Don't touch my beer.

18:40.570 --> 18:42.113
Do you hate her that much?

18:43.531 --> 18:44.574
Why?

18:44.866 --> 18:46.326
Because she made you handle affairs?

18:46.409 --> 18:48.202
They're PM cases, not affairs.

18:49.120 --> 18:51.706
Ms. Joo doesn't know about me yet.

18:51.789 --> 18:53.666
I was working on something
on Team One.

18:54.375 --> 18:57.128
I put everything in the folder
and when she sees that

18:58.421 --> 19:00.423
she'll see how good I am
and reappoint me.

19:00.506 --> 19:01.674
If she's that competent.

19:03.718 --> 19:04.802
Think about it.

19:05.094 --> 19:07.805
She wouldn't want to waste
talent like mine on stupid cases.

19:07.889 --> 19:10.266
Why not? I think
you're perfect for the job.

19:10.808 --> 19:12.393
To handle the PM cheaters.

19:12.477 --> 19:13.853
Why me?

19:16.314 --> 19:17.774
- Hang on.
- You are

19:18.107 --> 19:19.484
the best one for the job.

19:22.612 --> 19:23.655
Hey.

19:24.947 --> 19:27.241
That's exactly what Joo In-a said,
that I was the best for the job.

19:28.242 --> 19:30.787
- Why am I best for the job?
- It's about couples in love.

19:31.496 --> 19:34.499
- That's your expertise.
- What does she know about me?

19:35.333 --> 19:37.377
We just met. She can't know...

19:39.587 --> 19:40.630
No way.

19:41.381 --> 19:42.465
That retreating figure...

19:46.969 --> 19:48.096
Did she see me?

19:50.932 --> 19:52.809
So the reason she chose me...

19:54.811 --> 19:55.853
was that?

19:58.815 --> 20:00.566
No, it can't be.

20:02.610 --> 20:03.653
Can it be?

20:05.488 --> 20:06.489
Is it?

20:08.199 --> 20:09.367
Long, straight hair.

20:10.660 --> 20:11.786
A white shirt.

20:19.669 --> 20:20.920
It's practically a uniform.

20:40.106 --> 20:41.190
I can't say for sure.

20:42.400 --> 20:43.568
I don't think it was her.

20:51.409 --> 20:52.744
Why were you staring at me?

20:54.036 --> 20:55.288
Is a ghost haunting me?

20:55.371 --> 20:56.748
I came to make myself some coffee.

20:59.375 --> 21:01.711
You look like
you have something to say.

21:02.044 --> 21:03.171
Mr. Noh.

21:03.254 --> 21:05.673
If you have any concerns,
you can come to me freely.

21:07.216 --> 21:09.427
Yes, rather than driving myself crazy

21:09.510 --> 21:10.678
I'll ask her and clear the air.

21:11.220 --> 21:12.930
- Ms. Joo.
- Wait.

21:15.475 --> 21:17.685
I can't ask if she saw me kiss.

21:19.604 --> 21:20.605
What is it?

21:22.273 --> 21:23.900
What should we do
about the basement parking lot?

21:23.983 --> 21:27.570
We've confirmed through our humint
that it's a real issue.

21:27.945 --> 21:30.490
Shall we put up a sign saying
personal misconduct isn't allowed?

21:30.573 --> 21:31.783
We can't say we did any work, then.

21:32.325 --> 21:34.535
- We have to expose them.
- Expose?

21:34.744 --> 21:36.537
How am I going to do that?

21:36.621 --> 21:38.331
I can't go on a stakeout
just to wait for it.

21:38.414 --> 21:39.415
A stakeout?

21:39.749 --> 21:41.000
A stakeout?

21:41.334 --> 21:43.795
Why would you say something
so nonsensical?

21:43.878 --> 21:47.089
We're not detectives.
Why would we go on a stakeout?

21:47.882 --> 21:49.967
- Right, exactly.
- Exactly.

21:50.301 --> 21:52.303
I heard that someone
on the Audit Team

21:52.386 --> 21:54.722
flew a drone and took photos.

21:55.056 --> 21:58.976
How could an auditor do that?
We're not some drone-flying club.

22:04.774 --> 22:06.192
Down your coffee and get moving.

22:07.318 --> 22:08.694
My poor legs.

22:11.113 --> 22:14.575
This was the only company car
left for us to take.

22:15.660 --> 22:18.287
Darn it. I should've brought my car.

22:18.746 --> 22:21.249
Still, if you push the seat
back a bit

22:21.332 --> 22:22.542
it should free up some space.

22:22.625 --> 22:24.377
- No, it's fine.
- Let me help you.

22:24.669 --> 22:26.212
It's fine, really. I...

22:29.799 --> 22:31.425
I'm so sorry, Mr. Noh.

22:48.109 --> 22:49.986
Jeez, what the heck
are we even doing?

22:50.987 --> 22:52.655
Okay, Hyun-kyu.

22:53.030 --> 22:56.200
You didn't do all that studying
for your degree

22:56.993 --> 22:58.828
just to do this kind of job, did you?

23:00.454 --> 23:03.958
Unlike you,
I didn't go to a good university

23:04.041 --> 23:05.793
nor have great credentials.

23:06.919 --> 23:08.671
I barely got this job
because I'm from the area

23:08.754 --> 23:10.214
where Haemu built a huge factory.

23:10.673 --> 23:12.341
Oh, during my interview I said

23:13.092 --> 23:14.635
"White blood runs through my veins."

23:15.928 --> 23:18.306
That's how I introduced myself,
and they liked how I was different.

23:20.808 --> 23:22.935
- "White blood."
- White blood.

23:24.437 --> 23:26.147
- By white, you meant Haemu's color?
- Yes.

23:26.772 --> 23:28.566
That's why they call you
"White Blood Cell."

23:28.649 --> 23:29.650
That's right.

23:33.195 --> 23:36.949
You know, competent people like you

23:37.033 --> 23:39.994
might feel bored
by what our team does.

23:40.077 --> 23:43.247
But working at Haemu
which everyone envies

23:43.331 --> 23:47.919
and being on the Audit Team,
the best team in the company

23:48.210 --> 23:50.338
makes me pleased and proud.

24:04.602 --> 24:05.811
Hey, White Blood Cell.

24:06.228 --> 24:07.271
Yes, Mr. Noh?

24:08.022 --> 24:10.524
I didn't doze off.
I was only blinking for a long time.

24:10.608 --> 24:11.651
Do you remember

24:12.318 --> 24:13.819
the day Ms. Joo first joined?

24:18.491 --> 24:20.826
Do you know what she was wearing?

24:21.786 --> 24:23.079
Just a moment.

24:23.621 --> 24:26.415
- I remember such details perfectly.
- Do you?

24:27.667 --> 24:29.043
See if you can remember.

24:30.628 --> 24:31.629
What was she wearing?

24:32.964 --> 24:34.090
She wore

24:36.050 --> 24:37.218
black pants.

24:39.595 --> 24:41.639
What about her top?

24:42.098 --> 24:43.140
Her top...

24:44.684 --> 24:45.726
It was black.

24:47.186 --> 24:48.479
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

24:51.107 --> 24:52.149
It was black.

24:55.361 --> 24:56.404
Or not.

24:57.822 --> 24:59.407
I think it was a white shirt.

25:00.658 --> 25:01.659
Hey.

25:03.077 --> 25:04.078
Are you saying she wore white?

25:06.205 --> 25:07.289
Maybe not.

25:07.832 --> 25:09.667
- What?
- Was it black?

25:10.584 --> 25:12.628
- Was it black?
- No.

25:13.713 --> 25:14.755
It was white.

25:15.339 --> 25:16.382
Yes, white.

25:17.466 --> 25:18.592
Why, you!

25:21.012 --> 25:22.054
It was definitely white.

25:23.472 --> 25:24.557
Am I mistaken?

25:25.725 --> 25:27.059
Forget I even asked.

25:27.852 --> 25:30.938
- I'll go get coffee, so sober up.
- Okay.

25:59.133 --> 26:01.343
I have a bad feeling about this.

26:04.722 --> 26:06.474
Gosh, what am I even doing?

26:07.516 --> 26:09.852
So what if she saw it? I don't care.

26:10.311 --> 26:13.355
It's not like I committed a crime.
Forget it.

26:14.315 --> 26:15.357
Oh, my gosh.

26:17.818 --> 26:19.070
Why are you so startled?

26:22.573 --> 26:23.949
You walked in so suddenly.

26:25.910 --> 26:27.745
Can't I walk in suddenly?

26:28.329 --> 26:29.997
Should I have knocked?

26:32.875 --> 26:33.959
What?

26:34.543 --> 26:35.544
Were you

26:37.671 --> 26:38.839
doing this again?

26:57.441 --> 26:58.526
What was that?

27:00.694 --> 27:03.239
So she saw it. She saw everything.

27:42.570 --> 27:43.612
Noh Ki-jun.

27:45.364 --> 27:46.448
What do you want?

27:46.991 --> 27:48.492
You told me to ignore you at work.

27:48.576 --> 27:50.035
It's just us now.

27:50.703 --> 27:52.329
Is it Joo In-a again?

27:52.621 --> 27:53.747
You look half-dead.

27:53.831 --> 27:54.832
Yes.

27:55.374 --> 27:57.168
Bury me on a sunny slope.

27:58.127 --> 27:59.587
Why are you thinking
of getting buried?

28:00.212 --> 28:01.505
You have a lifeline.

28:02.047 --> 28:03.132
Director Kim.

28:04.008 --> 28:06.177
His dinner with the VP got canceled

28:06.260 --> 28:07.887
and he seemed to be looking
for a drinking buddy.

28:24.445 --> 28:25.738
Hello, Director Kim.

28:26.488 --> 28:28.657
It's Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

28:36.373 --> 28:41.086
Ms. Joo talks back
to every senior executive.

28:41.337 --> 28:43.923
Does she think I'm staying still
because I can't speak up?

28:44.340 --> 28:47.218
- I'm just keeping my boundaries.
- Yes, you're right.

28:48.219 --> 28:49.803
Is she rude to the executives, too?

28:50.638 --> 28:53.807
I guess she's not the type
to bow to the powerful.

28:53.891 --> 28:58.479
I don't care how she treats
the powerful or powerless.

28:59.647 --> 29:00.731
And there's you.

29:00.814 --> 29:03.192
She has such
a poor judgment of character.

29:03.651 --> 29:06.654
You're our ace, Mr. Noh.

29:06.737 --> 29:08.697
Yet she dumped you in Team Three.

29:09.114 --> 29:12.076
Now, you're handling PM cases.
What the heck is PM, anyway?

29:12.159 --> 29:13.160
Exactly.

29:13.827 --> 29:15.788
I'm having the worst time, sir.

29:16.121 --> 29:18.874
Don't you worry about that.

29:19.792 --> 29:20.793
You know who I am.

29:21.794 --> 29:24.088
Let me tell you something

29:24.546 --> 29:26.465
that's still off the record.

29:32.554 --> 29:35.683
I'm working to create
a new department.

29:37.101 --> 29:43.732
It'll serve as the control tower
of the whole organization.

29:44.733 --> 29:47.027
Business General... No.

29:47.111 --> 29:50.155
It's called
the General Business Control HQ.

29:50.239 --> 29:52.866
General Business Control HQ.

29:54.201 --> 29:56.036
- What a great name.
- Right?

29:57.705 --> 29:59.832
I said I wanted you on the team.

30:00.666 --> 30:03.460
You'll be able to escape soon.

30:07.923 --> 30:10.175
- Let me pour you a drink, sir.
- Okay.

30:13.095 --> 30:14.722
A toast

30:15.389 --> 30:18.309
to our General Business

30:18.392 --> 30:20.519
- Control HQ.
- Control HQ.

30:20.686 --> 30:24.023
- Let's drink to its bright future.
- Cheers!

30:33.240 --> 30:34.450
I'm in the mood.

30:48.672 --> 30:49.757
I'm heading home.

30:49.840 --> 30:51.425
Bye. See you tomorrow.

30:55.346 --> 30:57.598
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM
ASSISTANT MANAGER KWON HYUN-WOO

30:57.681 --> 30:59.016
It's raining.

30:59.099 --> 31:00.142
When do you get off work?

31:03.729 --> 31:04.772
I'm working late.

31:05.147 --> 31:06.440
Buy an umbrella and head home.

31:25.584 --> 31:26.752
Hello?

31:30.631 --> 31:31.632
Jun-seo?

31:33.926 --> 31:35.386
We did that all the time.

31:36.345 --> 31:37.471
Back then...

31:38.764 --> 31:40.057
we were young and rash.

31:40.641 --> 31:41.809
I'm glad I called you.

31:50.067 --> 31:52.027
Are you sure
you don't need to eat dinner?

31:52.486 --> 31:54.238
You love to eat.

31:54.947 --> 31:56.698
I'm okay with anything
if I'm with you.

32:01.036 --> 32:02.079
Right.

32:07.167 --> 32:08.544
It's pouring.

32:17.678 --> 32:19.346
- Why don't we...
- Yes?

32:20.013 --> 32:21.056
stay together?

32:22.266 --> 32:23.517
Just until the rain stops.

32:53.839 --> 32:55.174
SEND
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM, KWON HYUN-WOO

32:58.177 --> 32:59.344
Sent.

33:01.054 --> 33:02.389
Great work.

33:02.723 --> 33:04.141
My gosh. You must be tired.

33:04.391 --> 33:05.517
Great work until late.

33:05.601 --> 33:07.978
Don't mention it. I'm feeling proud.

33:08.395 --> 33:10.063
Today was
the first overtime of my life.

33:10.981 --> 33:11.982
Really?

33:12.608 --> 33:13.650
In that case

33:14.151 --> 33:15.402
why don't we grab a drink
to celebrate?

33:15.486 --> 33:16.778
I'd love to.

33:17.070 --> 33:18.363
Let's eat
something delicious, Mr. Kwon.

33:18.447 --> 33:20.365
- Okay, let's wrap up and leave.
- Great!

33:29.249 --> 33:30.584
WIFE

33:41.261 --> 33:42.638
I said you could leave first.

33:46.225 --> 33:47.267
Were you rained on?

33:54.233 --> 33:55.484
We shouldn't do this.

34:00.739 --> 34:02.157
The rain has stopped.

34:04.451 --> 34:05.452
Let's do it.

34:05.994 --> 34:07.579
- What?
- Let's do it.

34:09.039 --> 34:10.541
We can't keep going like this.
We have to do it.

34:11.166 --> 34:12.376
What's with you?

34:15.087 --> 34:17.381
All right. Let's go home first.
You're going to catch a cold.

34:18.549 --> 34:19.591
Let's do it here.

34:20.050 --> 34:21.843
It's that area. Zone F.

34:32.437 --> 34:33.438
Hey.

34:39.987 --> 34:41.613
- What's with you?
- Be quiet.

35:22.195 --> 35:23.530
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

35:23.614 --> 35:25.157
The president approved!

35:25.240 --> 35:27.909
You'll be out of the Audit Team
within days, Mr. Noh.

35:27.993 --> 35:30.454
Director Kim, you're awesome!

35:34.124 --> 35:36.335
I'm the best

35:37.836 --> 35:39.588
I'm the best

35:40.881 --> 35:42.966
- Are you getting off early today?
- I'll try to.

35:43.300 --> 35:44.509
- Let's eat something good.
- Okay.

35:44.885 --> 35:46.803
- Try to clock out quickly.
- Okay.

35:51.642 --> 35:54.019
- Hello. Good morning.
- Hello.

35:59.149 --> 36:01.401
- The weather's great, isn't it?
- Yes.

36:02.319 --> 36:04.946
You're looking extra sharp today.

36:05.656 --> 36:06.865
- Do I?
- Yes.

36:07.616 --> 36:09.576
You two look great, too.

36:10.911 --> 36:12.329
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

36:24.800 --> 36:25.801
Hello, Ms. Joo.

36:26.385 --> 36:27.844
Hey, Mr. Noh. Good morning.

36:28.303 --> 36:30.639
You must like dress shirts.
You look good in them.

36:32.724 --> 36:33.934
You're looking happy.

36:34.393 --> 36:35.936
Did something great happen
this morning?

36:36.186 --> 36:38.105
There's no reason
to be in a foul mood.

36:38.188 --> 36:39.523
Look at that great weather.

36:39.606 --> 36:40.982
There is a reason, actually.

36:42.067 --> 36:44.194
You haven't caught
a single case in the parking garage.

36:45.320 --> 36:47.656
You won't take matters lightly
just like you did

36:47.739 --> 36:49.366
with Mr. Son's case, will you?

36:50.534 --> 36:51.576
Keep it up, will you?

36:51.660 --> 36:54.454
Every assignment is important
here in the Audit Team.

36:55.539 --> 36:58.750
Fine, I'll go along. I won't have
to see her for much longer.

36:59.042 --> 37:00.335
Yes, of course.

37:00.627 --> 37:02.963
I even brought my car
to stake out properly.

37:03.422 --> 37:05.048
Will I ever let you down again?

37:06.174 --> 37:07.342
No, never.

37:15.684 --> 37:16.768
Ms. Joo.

37:17.144 --> 37:20.230
There was a huge lucky draw
at our online mall recently

37:20.439 --> 37:23.024
and people are asking
how the winners were decided

37:23.108 --> 37:25.235
or if the draw was even real,
and some are complaining

37:25.318 --> 37:27.070
that they didn't win
even after many tries.

37:27.154 --> 37:29.865
It's not like the Audit Team
is the customer service center.

37:29.948 --> 37:32.701
Mr. Noh, you can continue
to work on the parking lot case.

37:33.034 --> 37:34.286
Wait a second.

37:34.745 --> 37:36.997
You'll need a partner
for your stakeout, won't you?

37:37.706 --> 37:39.583
Goodness. One second.

37:40.500 --> 37:43.128
White Blood Cell is on the phone too.
We don't have enough manpower.

37:44.713 --> 37:46.298
We do, Mr. Moo.

37:46.965 --> 37:48.633
We have our strongest asset here.

37:50.510 --> 37:51.511
Who?

37:59.770 --> 38:01.563
You're making me feel uncomfortable.
Cut it out.

38:03.982 --> 38:07.110
Why? Is the parking lot case
not quite suitable for you?

38:09.362 --> 38:12.657
But you told me that every case here
is equally important.

38:18.079 --> 38:19.247
Shall I do that, then?

38:19.998 --> 38:22.542
Let's spend some quality time alone.

38:30.801 --> 38:32.385
You don't need to buckle up.

38:33.261 --> 38:34.304
I'm not starting the car.

38:37.140 --> 38:38.266
It's my decision.

38:38.350 --> 38:40.060
Come on. You forgot, didn't you?

38:40.560 --> 38:42.270
Unbuckle it.
It must be uncomfortable.

38:42.354 --> 38:44.231
No, I'm not uncomfortable at all.

38:44.314 --> 38:46.358
I feel so comfortable right now.

38:46.441 --> 38:48.610
Unbuckle it. You don't need
to play it cool over this matter.

38:50.821 --> 38:52.155
Things happen.

38:52.531 --> 38:55.450
Stakeouts are for people
who are experienced.

38:55.659 --> 38:56.868
It's all right.

38:59.204 --> 39:02.791
I knew it. Your understanding
of these assignments is very high.

39:02.874 --> 39:03.875
Sorry?

39:05.126 --> 39:07.003
I'm sure you know a thing or two

39:07.087 --> 39:09.422
about cases like this one.

39:12.801 --> 39:13.844
Ms. Joo.

39:14.553 --> 39:17.681
- Back then, that...
- That? What do you mean by that?

39:17.764 --> 39:19.975
That. Whatever it is you saw.

39:20.350 --> 39:21.393
It wasn't that...

39:21.977 --> 39:24.271
I'm not that kind of person.

39:24.521 --> 39:26.314
My lips were also...

39:27.399 --> 39:28.441
Quiet.

39:29.901 --> 39:30.944
Over there.

39:55.135 --> 39:56.136
Okay.

40:11.067 --> 40:13.361
I'll wrap it up. It's my job.

40:25.790 --> 40:28.043
I'll open the door.
I'm from the Audit Team.

40:37.010 --> 40:38.553
I'm opening the door.

40:46.311 --> 40:48.647
Oh, my. Director Kim!

40:49.147 --> 40:50.273
You said you were busy.

40:52.943 --> 40:55.320
- Wait.
- What are you two doing here?

40:55.403 --> 40:56.404
What's with you?

40:57.739 --> 41:00.200
You, of all people,
should know better.

41:00.283 --> 41:03.203
When you both have spouses,
don't you?

41:06.331 --> 41:08.625
Will you close that door?

41:09.668 --> 41:11.169
Wrap it up and come outside.

41:19.928 --> 41:21.388
I knew it, Mr. Noh.

41:21.638 --> 41:23.556
I knew you could do it!

41:24.140 --> 41:27.352
You caught a big one.
He's a big fish!

41:27.852 --> 41:30.021
This is why you're the ace
of the Audit Team.

41:31.189 --> 41:32.232
Let's see.

41:32.565 --> 41:35.944
Director Kim was
formerly your direct superior.

41:38.279 --> 41:41.116
You took down your former superior
whom you worked with for years

41:41.783 --> 41:43.618
like a cold-blooded man!

41:44.285 --> 41:45.912
If only everyone else were like you

41:45.996 --> 41:49.749
this world would've been
a much better place.

41:57.215 --> 41:58.466
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

41:59.009 --> 42:01.761
Is there a possibility
that Director Kim will be let off

42:01.845 --> 42:04.180
- just like Mr. Son?
- No.

42:04.597 --> 42:06.474
This is a different case.

42:07.058 --> 42:09.602
He's an executive, so we can revoke
his contract and fire him right away.

42:09.686 --> 42:11.021
Fire him?

42:12.022 --> 42:14.607
But Director Kim is also
a necessary part of the company...

42:14.691 --> 42:16.109
Not at all.

42:16.443 --> 42:18.570
He's an old-timer with an ego
who sits around doing nothing

42:18.653 --> 42:20.030
only because
he's close to the president.

42:20.864 --> 42:22.615
He must've been an eyesore
to the vice president.

42:23.867 --> 42:27.454
You just gave him
a wonderful reason to fire that man.

42:32.792 --> 42:33.918
Director Kim

42:36.296 --> 42:37.297
is done for.

43:06.034 --> 43:08.411
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

43:11.122 --> 43:13.917
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to...

43:26.054 --> 43:28.848
ELDEST SISTER
ACCEPT

43:28.932 --> 43:30.600
- Hilarious.
- Hey.

43:31.142 --> 43:33.978
Hello, Ki-jun? When are you coming?

43:34.771 --> 43:36.731
I'm on my way, and I'm almost there.

43:41.277 --> 43:44.155
Ki-jun, we have to change
the bathroom doorknob, too.

43:44.447 --> 43:45.490
Okay.

43:47.117 --> 43:48.159
Hey, Ki-jun!

43:48.576 --> 43:50.370
Take a look at Jin-yeong's laptop.

43:50.954 --> 43:52.664
- Laptop?
- Hey, Ki-jun.

43:52.747 --> 43:54.249
That couch has been wobbling.
Take a look.

43:54.624 --> 43:57.460
I'm only one man,
so talk to me one at a time.

43:59.170 --> 44:00.171
The couch?

44:02.215 --> 44:04.008
- Which side is wobbly?
- The left.

44:04.092 --> 44:05.343
Goodness.

44:07.470 --> 44:11.099
Goodness, I'm so proud of you,
my youngest one.

44:13.768 --> 44:15.728
Cut it out, Mom.

44:21.985 --> 44:23.528
Mom, this meat is delicious.

44:27.157 --> 44:29.075
Hey, Ki-jun.
Why are you drinking so much?

44:29.159 --> 44:30.910
Look at him.
He hasn't even eaten his food.

44:30.994 --> 44:32.245
You can't even hold your alcohol.

44:33.413 --> 44:36.291
- Stop drinking.
- Stop pinching me, please!

44:37.000 --> 44:38.293
Will you just leave me alone?

44:38.376 --> 44:39.878
Is something going on, Ki-jun?

44:40.128 --> 44:41.421
Right? What's wrong?

44:42.088 --> 44:43.715
Hey, is someone bullying you?

44:44.757 --> 44:47.635
What? Hey, who is it?
Who's that punk?

44:47.719 --> 44:49.596
Hey, go file a lawsuit.

44:49.679 --> 44:51.347
- Talk to her husband!
- I'll talk to him.

44:51.431 --> 44:53.391
We have to talk it out first.
Do you want me to make a call?

44:53.474 --> 44:55.894
Please stop this and leave me alone.

44:55.977 --> 44:57.896
We need the name first. Who is it?

44:57.979 --> 45:00.023
- We have to talk it out first.
- Talk what out?

45:00.106 --> 45:01.900
Look at this kid.

45:01.983 --> 45:04.194
Call your husband first, okay?

45:04.277 --> 45:07.322
Who's the punk that did this
to my precious son?

45:08.031 --> 45:09.324
- You...
- Darn it.

45:09.407 --> 45:10.742
- Who is it?
- Talk it out.

45:10.825 --> 45:12.827
- Hey, tell me who it is.
- We need the name first.

45:12.911 --> 45:14.787
- What's the name?
- Mom, listen.

45:14.871 --> 45:16.956
- We need the name first.
- We need that.

45:17.040 --> 45:18.291
- Who is it?
- Why won't he pick up?

45:18.374 --> 45:19.667
- Get the name.
- We need the name.

45:19.751 --> 45:21.127
You all need to stop.

45:21.211 --> 45:23.004
- Who is it? Tell me!
- Hear me out.

45:23.087 --> 45:25.882
- Ki-jun.
- I hate all three of you!

45:25.965 --> 45:28.218
Just leave me alone!

45:28.301 --> 45:30.720
No, bring her phone to me.

45:30.929 --> 45:33.139
- Is he not picking up?
- Call the customer service line.

45:33.223 --> 45:35.725
- The customer service?
- We need to reach someone!

45:50.865 --> 45:53.076
HAEMU PHARMACEUTICAL
2025 CONTRACT INSPECTION

45:53.159 --> 45:54.869
2024 FUND EXECUTION INSPECTION

45:58.248 --> 45:59.916
NOH KI-JUN, AUDIT TEAM 1 TURNOVER

45:59.999 --> 46:04.712
DO YOU WISH TO PERMANENTLY DELETE
ALL FOLDERS AND FILES?

46:24.482 --> 46:27.026
I'm sorry about Director Kim.

46:27.110 --> 46:29.195
- Did you dig him up intentionally?
- No.

46:30.154 --> 46:31.614
It was a coincidence
from another case.

46:31.698 --> 46:32.699
How disappointing.

46:32.991 --> 46:34.701
I thought you finally learned
to wield your sword

46:34.784 --> 46:35.910
but it was sheer luck.

46:37.203 --> 46:39.080
I haven't given you anything yet.

46:39.747 --> 46:40.790
Prove yourself

46:41.499 --> 46:42.792
that you're different from your mom.

47:06.524 --> 47:08.818
Honey, Sung-yeol is here.

47:10.194 --> 47:12.405
You should say hi to him.
I'll go and make coffee.

47:15.199 --> 47:17.035
Father, your youngest son is here.

47:18.703 --> 47:21.372
- And so are you, Jae-yeol.
- It's been a while.

47:23.833 --> 47:25.168
How's your health, Father?

47:25.710 --> 47:27.879
I've exiled you
and haven't called you back.

47:28.296 --> 47:29.922
How dare you show yourself here?

47:30.006 --> 47:31.632
It's great to see
that you're the same.

47:34.344 --> 47:36.429
How come there is
no middle ground between you two?

47:36.846 --> 47:39.182
One of you is too soft
to do anything substantial

47:39.515 --> 47:43.019
and the other is too reckless,
causing trouble everywhere.

47:43.436 --> 47:44.437
Darn it.

47:46.022 --> 47:48.149
You see, Father

47:49.150 --> 47:50.651
I have caused yet another trouble.

47:52.362 --> 47:54.864
It's the gas plant in Saudi Arabia
that you've even dreamed of.

47:54.947 --> 47:57.950
I got the first package,
and on top of that the third one.

47:58.284 --> 48:00.995
The entire project
is worth 8.77 billion dollars.

48:01.913 --> 48:03.039
And I got it.

48:10.254 --> 48:13.174
So? Isn't this good enough
to put an end to my exile?

48:14.509 --> 48:16.469
I hear there's a spot open
in the head office.

48:32.860 --> 48:34.195
Should I cancel the luncheon?

48:34.570 --> 48:36.030
You do not look well.

48:37.281 --> 48:38.324
I'm fine.

48:40.910 --> 48:42.870
I need personnel evaluation reports

48:43.371 --> 48:45.081
and a list of potential staff
up for a promotion.

48:45.873 --> 48:46.916
Also, set up

48:47.458 --> 48:50.378
a dinner with QS International's
President Lee Hyeong-geun

48:50.753 --> 48:51.754
as soon as possible.

48:52.296 --> 48:53.506
I understand.

48:54.799 --> 48:57.301
Would you like to leave right away
for the AI camp?

48:58.386 --> 48:59.387
In half an hour.

49:01.722 --> 49:02.807
One second.

49:24.912 --> 49:26.372
I can do this for myself.

49:27.999 --> 49:29.167
E-mail me the files.

49:32.753 --> 49:33.754
Yes, sir.

50:11.667 --> 50:14.045
- What now?
- I'm telling you.

50:17.256 --> 50:18.799
Goodness, I need some sugar.

50:21.761 --> 50:22.762
My gosh.

50:24.680 --> 50:27.642
Where was Ms. Yoon's snack box again?

50:29.143 --> 50:31.145
There it is. Ms. Yoon's snack box.

50:32.313 --> 50:35.483
Goodness. It's heavy.
Did you get something new?

50:36.859 --> 50:38.444
Hey, these are new.

50:42.573 --> 50:43.574
It's good.

50:44.909 --> 50:45.952
- Mango-flavored?
- Yes.

50:46.285 --> 50:48.704
Hey, Hae-young. Where are we
having team dinner again?

50:48.788 --> 50:50.248
Piggy's Charcoal BBQ.

50:50.331 --> 50:51.332
We're having pork again?

50:51.832 --> 50:54.502
Can we get something better?
It's Ms. Joo's welcome party.

50:54.585 --> 50:56.879
Our budget for team dinners
is running low this year.

50:57.171 --> 50:58.631
Ms. Pyun.

50:59.048 --> 51:01.217
Why do you act like
a stingy mother-in-law

51:01.300 --> 51:04.053
who never lets anyone near her money
with the company fund?

51:05.179 --> 51:07.348
There's a servant
that's trying to clean out the fund

51:07.682 --> 51:09.016
so I have no other choice, Mr. Moo.

51:09.100 --> 51:10.101
- What?
- Servant?

51:10.434 --> 51:11.477
You heard her, right?

51:11.561 --> 51:13.020
Did you just call me a servant?

51:13.104 --> 51:15.773
- Do you feel guilty?
- Technically, we're all servants.

51:16.774 --> 51:17.858
Anyway.

51:18.442 --> 51:20.069
Where's Mr. Noh?
He's been away for a while.

51:20.152 --> 51:22.613
Mr. Noh didn't seem well.

51:22.697 --> 51:25.491
He doesn't look well,
he keeps sighing

51:25.866 --> 51:28.536
and his eyes looked a bit watery too.

51:29.120 --> 51:31.539
- Anyway, he looks quite sad.
- Really?

51:32.623 --> 51:34.792
- Did he get dumped?
- I think so.

51:34.875 --> 51:37.003
Goodness. That's heartbreaking.

51:41.549 --> 51:42.925
Thanks a lot.

52:03.195 --> 52:04.238
He is

52:04.864 --> 52:05.948
leaving.

52:11.621 --> 52:12.747
My hope.

52:14.123 --> 52:15.333
My lifeline.

52:18.336 --> 52:19.462
Adios.

52:20.838 --> 52:22.465
PIGGY'S CHARCOAL BBQ

52:22.548 --> 52:23.549
Hello.

52:23.758 --> 52:24.925
Thank you.

52:31.307 --> 52:33.726
It used to be a great spot.

52:34.727 --> 52:36.729
Back then, the front of the factory
used to be salt farms.

52:36.812 --> 52:38.481
It became a huge issue.

52:38.564 --> 52:40.816
What's the most important
when it comes to making salt?

52:40.900 --> 52:41.984
Sunlight and wind.

52:42.652 --> 52:44.612
So if the southeastern direction
gets blocked off

52:45.154 --> 52:47.490
it creates a shadow
and stops the wind

52:47.573 --> 52:48.866
which stops salt from crystallizing.

52:49.533 --> 52:52.620
And the one who stepped up
as a troubleshooter was...

52:52.703 --> 52:53.788
Mr. Baek.

52:54.413 --> 52:57.375
- You should eat some, too.
- I've been eating. It's okay.

52:57.583 --> 53:00.836
You're making me look rude.

53:00.920 --> 53:02.129
After all, I'm the youngest.

53:03.798 --> 53:05.466
No, it's all right, really.

53:05.925 --> 53:08.511
Because everyone thinks
you're just like that.

53:08.594 --> 53:09.887
That I'm just rude?

53:11.639 --> 53:12.723
That wasn't what I meant.

53:13.891 --> 53:15.559
The meat is burning. Have some.

53:16.102 --> 53:18.854
- And Mr. Oh is such an odd guy.
- You just dissed me.

53:18.938 --> 53:22.066
This happened during the early days
of his time in China.

53:22.149 --> 53:23.150
Really?

53:23.901 --> 53:25.611
What do you mean?
I haven't said anything.

53:25.695 --> 53:27.738
- I can't believe it.
- Wait, it's not that.

53:27.947 --> 53:30.157
Will you listen up?
Anyway, this guy...

53:30.700 --> 53:31.867
All right.

53:32.076 --> 53:34.870
Audit Team Three,
why don't we make a toast?

53:34.954 --> 53:36.664
Hello, Ms. Joo.

53:37.498 --> 53:38.791
Thank you.

53:39.792 --> 53:42.878
- Shall we have a toast?
- One second, please.

53:43.170 --> 53:44.255
Goodness.

53:45.423 --> 53:47.258
- Yes, drink up.
- I will.

53:47.341 --> 53:48.968
We're all here
to make a living, aren't we?

53:49.051 --> 53:50.344
- Thank you.
- Sure.

53:50.970 --> 53:53.097
- Now, would you like a drink?
- Yes, Ms. Joo.

53:53.264 --> 53:55.307
- Drink up.
- Thank you.

53:59.311 --> 54:01.063
Mr. Noh, why don't you
have a drink, too?

54:08.112 --> 54:09.405
You want soju?

54:10.072 --> 54:11.115
Okay.

54:12.324 --> 54:14.827
You've done well, Mr. Noh.

54:17.329 --> 54:19.749
You all know
that Mr. Noh got someone big, right?

54:19.832 --> 54:20.833
Yes, of course.

54:20.916 --> 54:22.668
Mr. Noh is the pride of our team!

54:22.752 --> 54:25.504
He says you're the pride.

54:26.255 --> 54:28.507
Why don't we make a toast to Mr. Noh,
the ace of Audit Team Three?

54:28.799 --> 54:30.426
- Shall we?
- Goodness.

54:30.509 --> 54:31.719
All right.

54:32.470 --> 54:34.388
To Mr. Noh.

54:34.472 --> 54:36.515
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

54:36.599 --> 54:38.476
- Cheers!
- All right, Mr. Noh!

54:41.103 --> 54:42.396
That's nice.

54:43.314 --> 54:44.315
Gosh.

54:45.107 --> 54:47.109
That's a nice drink.

54:47.818 --> 54:48.861
May I?

54:50.154 --> 54:51.197
A lettuce wrap, Ms. Joo.

54:51.280 --> 54:54.325
I need you baby, bye bye bye

54:54.408 --> 54:57.995
Must you go, why why why?

54:58.078 --> 55:00.915
All you said was a lie lie lie

55:00.998 --> 55:03.834
I will wait

55:03.918 --> 55:07.421
Until the day I die

55:07.922 --> 55:13.093
Do not cry alone
Because I am not there

55:14.136 --> 55:16.680
Goodbye

55:19.892 --> 55:22.937
Come back

55:23.020 --> 55:26.816
My dear

55:27.900 --> 55:31.445
Do you not know

55:32.071 --> 55:34.114
- These songs are killing the vibe.
- Right?

55:35.658 --> 55:39.119
May I resuscitate the mood
as the head of this organization?

55:41.080 --> 55:42.957
Drop that microphone now.

55:44.124 --> 55:46.210
Come back here, Mr. Noh.

55:46.877 --> 55:49.171
It's "Twit"!

55:49.255 --> 55:50.256
Okay!

55:59.348 --> 56:00.808
You're a fool

56:01.934 --> 56:03.853
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

56:03.936 --> 56:05.187
I don't like it

56:05.271 --> 56:07.857
Nobody likes it
The delicate Sim Cheong

56:08.983 --> 56:10.985
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

56:11.068 --> 56:13.863
I don't like it
Nobody likes it

56:14.196 --> 56:15.614
You're a fool

56:16.615 --> 56:18.826
All you care about is yourself

56:19.910 --> 56:23.414
The delicate Sim Cheong

56:23.622 --> 56:24.874
Try to look around

56:25.583 --> 56:28.419
You're in pain but you have no idea

56:28.878 --> 56:30.546
You make me royal
You make me a hero

56:30.629 --> 56:31.964
You make me a genius, yes

56:32.256 --> 56:35.509
You give a lot
But why do you always end up unhappy?

56:35.885 --> 56:39.096
Because you only breathe for yourself

56:41.640 --> 56:43.100
You're a fool

56:43.183 --> 56:46.186
- Yeah! Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

56:46.270 --> 56:49.315
I don't like it
Nobody likes it

56:55.154 --> 56:56.363
Ms. Joo In-a.

56:57.489 --> 56:59.325
Don't you think this is too much?

57:06.415 --> 57:07.416
Fine.

57:08.250 --> 57:09.877
I kissed.

57:11.503 --> 57:14.214
I know that's why you put me
in charge of PM.

57:15.466 --> 57:16.967
But what's so bad about that?

57:17.968 --> 57:21.555
Why is that misconduct?

57:23.015 --> 57:24.642
Does anyone here never kiss?

57:25.601 --> 57:26.644
Ever?

57:26.727 --> 57:28.812
Don't you ever kiss?

57:29.229 --> 57:31.231
Don't you kiss, too?

58:24.493 --> 58:25.536
Are you okay?

58:25.911 --> 58:27.121
You threw up all night.

58:29.581 --> 58:30.874
I heard
you dropped a bomb last night.

58:31.500 --> 58:32.751
How did you know?

58:32.835 --> 58:34.169
We are a company.

58:34.253 --> 58:36.338
Something fun like that
goes around in real-time.

58:37.923 --> 58:39.842
You've never been
the object of hatred, have you?

58:40.217 --> 58:42.845
You're the beloved Noh Ki-jun,
whom everyone liked.

58:43.429 --> 58:44.596
Beloved, my foot.

58:50.519 --> 58:52.229
After all, it's just work.

58:52.980 --> 58:55.065
She'll forget someday
if I do my job well, right?

58:55.691 --> 58:56.692
Ki-jun.

58:57.192 --> 59:00.279
When you adore someone,
you adore them for no reason.

59:00.362 --> 59:03.407
But once you hate someone,
you hate them no matter what they do.

59:04.241 --> 59:07.369
I'm sure Ms. Joo thinks
you're her biggest eyesore right now

59:07.453 --> 59:08.454
no matter what you do.

59:09.663 --> 59:11.248
Should I just quit?

59:11.331 --> 59:13.167
You still need to get to work

59:13.709 --> 59:15.335
to turn in your resignation.

59:16.211 --> 59:17.379
I'm taking the day off.

59:18.338 --> 59:19.381
Good for you.

59:39.193 --> 59:40.611
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

59:41.779 --> 59:43.113
I apologize for last night.

59:43.322 --> 59:44.782
You must've been quite disappointed.

59:45.616 --> 59:46.617
Sorry?

59:49.578 --> 59:52.081
That you couldn't transfer
to General Business Control HQ.

59:55.334 --> 59:58.462
You should've talked to me
if you wanted to leave the team.

59:58.545 --> 01:00:00.089
I'm not that uptight.

01:00:01.006 --> 01:00:02.466
Instead of talking behind my back.

01:00:04.593 --> 01:00:07.429
Also, that department
is no longer in formation

01:00:07.513 --> 01:00:08.722
with Director Kim's dismissal.

01:00:18.732 --> 01:00:20.818
Are you feeling all right?

01:00:21.735 --> 01:00:23.237
I think

01:00:23.529 --> 01:00:26.031
you're really something, Mr. Noh.

01:00:26.240 --> 01:00:28.200
If I were you,
I could never come to work.

01:00:28.534 --> 01:00:30.452
Stop making matters worse.

01:00:31.411 --> 01:00:34.123
I'm sure it's hard enough for him.

01:00:34.373 --> 01:00:35.415
Isn't it?

01:00:38.127 --> 01:00:39.920
I guess he's the type who blows up.

01:00:48.804 --> 01:00:51.140
No, okay? That's not it.

01:01:03.110 --> 01:01:04.111
NOH KI-JUN

01:01:05.237 --> 01:01:06.905
CHECK SEVERANCE PAY

01:01:07.823 --> 01:01:09.491
SEVERANCE PAY: 40,788,560 WON

01:01:09.575 --> 01:01:10.576
All right.

01:01:10.784 --> 01:01:13.453
That's enough money
to last some time to get refreshed

01:01:13.537 --> 01:01:14.955
before I get another job.

01:01:16.039 --> 01:01:17.791
Dang it. I'll just quit.

01:01:19.960 --> 01:01:21.003
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

01:01:22.754 --> 01:01:24.131
NAME: NOH KI-JUN

01:01:24.214 --> 01:01:25.465
REQUESTED BY: NOH KI-JUN

01:01:38.145 --> 01:01:39.438
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

01:01:57.331 --> 01:01:58.957
Ms. Joo, I must talk to you.

01:02:01.460 --> 01:02:02.502
Mr. Noh.

01:02:02.920 --> 01:02:03.962
Mr. Noh!

01:02:07.341 --> 01:02:08.759
Did you take my printout?

01:02:10.510 --> 01:02:11.803
AUDIT TEAM 3 STATIONERY SPENDINGS

01:02:15.474 --> 01:02:16.475
One moment, please.

01:02:21.688 --> 01:02:22.814
Here.

01:02:40.123 --> 01:02:41.291
Jeez.

01:02:45.671 --> 01:02:47.506
YOU HAVE A NEW E-MAIL:
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

01:03:04.648 --> 01:03:06.692
HEAD OF AUDIT

01:03:07.359 --> 01:03:09.903
HEAD OF AUDIT JOO IN-A

01:03:14.950 --> 01:03:17.369
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

01:03:19.162 --> 01:03:22.874
MS. JOO IN-A IS INVOLVED

01:03:22.958 --> 01:03:27.421
IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

01:03:51.611 --> 01:03:54.531
FILING FOR LOVE

01:03:55.115 --> 01:03:57.993
GUEST APPEARANCES BY SHIN HYUN-SOO,
PYO YE-JIN, AND KIM JONG-TAE

01:04:24.227 --> 01:04:25.520
Did I get you?

01:04:26.355 --> 01:04:28.982
If that report turns out to be true

01:04:29.316 --> 01:04:31.902
that means I'll have what I need
to take Joo In-a down.

01:04:32.527 --> 01:04:33.570
- What?
- What is this?

01:04:33.653 --> 01:04:34.696
The Older Women Hunter?

01:04:34.780 --> 01:04:36.114
You need to stop, ma'am.

01:04:36.198 --> 01:04:37.824
Please leave immediately.

01:04:38.658 --> 01:04:40.202
Joo In-a couldn't possibly be
having an affair.

01:04:40.494 --> 01:04:43.121
Has she ever come with a man?

01:04:43.205 --> 01:04:45.374
Gosh, ten condoms?

01:04:45.457 --> 01:04:48.835
Our company is about to see
the biggest storm in history.

01:04:48.919 --> 01:04:51.880
What kind of person is Joo In-a?

01:05:04.893 --> 01:05:06.895
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
